    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2006 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine and a 6-speed manual transaxle. This unit has been mechanically sorted with a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a proactive replacement of the water pump and thermostat. The chassis utilizes Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), providing exceptional lateral stability and variable damping. The hydraulic power steering provides visceral feedback, paired with a communicative multi-link rear suspension for optimized power delivery on corner exit. The M96 powerplant maintains strong compression and linear power delivery through the rev range. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical components, drivetrain, and synchros remain in robust, high-functioning condition.",
      "price": 31500.0,
